ossprofitTurnover":20.59,"MaterialDmntr":128696128,"StockInTrade":2.4}},"Form3cdUnpaidStrySec43b3Info":{"CsvDtls":{"HasMoreThan500":"false","Attachment":{"mimetype":"text/csv","hash":"12345"}}},"OtherInformation1":{"PostOfficeName":"Tirupur H.O","AddrDetail2":"2ND STREETTIRUPPUR","FirstName":"SUBRAMANIAN","StateCode":"29","PostOffice":"93372","LocalityOrAreaName":"Tiruppur","MiddleName":"","LocalityOrArea":"391080","CityOrTownOrDistrict":"492","Date":"2024-08-31","PinCode":"641601","FirmRegNum":"0001893S","MembershipNo":"207277","IpAddress":"IpAddress","LastName":"DHANANJAYAN","AddrDetail1":"5VALIPALAYAM","CountryCode":"91","Place":"Tiruppur","attachmentDocument":[{"docName":"BS_V-904_2023-2024.pdf","docId":335429278,"docHash":"bcf756d69b8e2fd1d0a229efe39b9c02612b25d7cc8e3f11e8c7758265408b0a","docSize":182251,"contentType":"application/pdf"},{"docName":"PL_V-904_2023-2024.pdf","docId":335429280,"docHash":"30db7bc0c446e836cdc8faae05a4e97892485f71b403f6236c829ff38e8ae452","docSize":169414,"contentType":"application/pdf"}]},"Form3cdBreakUpGST":[{"CompSchme":315303,"GoodOrSerGST":5665435,"TotAmtExp":734043158,"RegEntities":575490366,"ExpNonRegGST":62044034,"OthRegEntities":569509628}],"Form3cdAmtInadm40ASubClauseiC":[0],"Form3cdAmtInadm40A2":[{"DateOfPayment":"2024-03-31","AddressDetails":{"AddrDetail2":"5, Valipalayam Second Street","StateCode":"29","AddrDetail1":"RG Chambers First Floor","CountryCode":"91","CityOrTownOrDistrict":"Tiruppur","PinCode":"641601"},"NatureOfPayment":"Professional Fees","ParticularType":"SUBCLAUSEia","AmtOfPayment":400000,"NameOfPayee":"MSS and Co","PANOfPayee":"AAHFM6223C"}],"Form3cdBooksOfAccLst":[{"Form3cdBooksOfAccLstPK":{"BooksOfAccType":"LBEX","BooksDetail":"Cash Book, Bank Book, General Ledger, Purchase Register, Sales Register Journal Register"}}],"CostAudit":{"CostAuditFlag":"N"},"Declaration":{"Point1":{"PointA":{"AuditEndDate":"2024-03-31","TypeOfAccount":"Profit and loss account","AuditStartDate":"2023-04-01"},"PointC":"Profit and loss account","DateofsigningTaxAuditReport":"2024-08-31","Me_Us_Ms":"Us","AuditYearDate":"2024-03-31","AddressDetail":{"PostOfficeName":"Nallur B.O","AddrDetail2":"Muthanapalayam Road,, S Nallur,","StateCode":"29","PostOffice":"801","LocalityOrAreaName":"MUTHANAMPALAYAM","AddrDetail1":"244/1, II-FLOOOR, Nallur","CountryCode":"91","LocalityOrArea":"367301","CityOrTownOrDistrict":"492","PinCode":"641606"},"Act":"14","AuditDated":"2024-08-15","My_Our_Their":"Our","AssesseeName":{"FirstName":"","LastName":"VELAV GARMENTS INDIA PRIVATE LIMITED","MiddleName":""},"CA_FirmName":"M/s MSS and Co., Chartered Accountants, Tiruppur.","I_We1":"We","PAN":"AAICV4929J","I_We2":"We"},"Point3":{"My_Our1":"Our","My_Our2":"Our","Me_Us":"Us","Observations":[{"ObservationsVal":"The assessee is responsible for the preparation of the statement of particulars required to be furnished under section 44AB of the Income-tax Act, 1961 annexed herewith in Form No. 3CD read with Rule 6 G (1) (b) of Income Tax Rules, 1962 that give true and correct particulars as per the provisions of the income-tax Act, 1961 read with Rules, Notifications, Circulars etc. that are to be included in the statement. This responsibility also includes designing, implementing and maintaining internal controls, that are relevant and operating effectively for the preparation and presentation of the particulars furnished in Form No. 3CD that are free from material misstatement, whether due to fraud or error.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"Our responsibility is to provide reasonable assurance about whether the particulars furnished in Form No. 3CD as a whole are free from material misstatement, whether due to fraud or error. We conducted our audit in accordance with the Standards on Auditing (SAs) issued by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI). In order to identify and assess the risk of material misstatement, we design and perform audit procedures responsive to those risks, and obtain audit evidence that is sufficient and appropriate to provide a basis for our opinion. Reasonable assurance is a high level of assurance, but is not a guarantee that an audit conducted in accordance with Standards on Auditing will always detect a material misstatement when it exists. Misstatements can arise from fraud or error and are considered material if, individually or in the aggregate, they could reasonably be expected to influence the economic decisions of users.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"As part of an audit in accordance with Standards on Auditing, we exercise professional judgement and maintain professional scepticism throughout the audit.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"We evaluate the appropriateness of accounting policies used and the reasonableness of the accounting estimates and related disclosures made by the assessee as well as evaluate the overall presentation, structure and content of the information.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"We are also responsible for verifying the statement of particulars required to be furnished under section 44AB of the Income-tax Act, 1961 annexed herewith in Form No. 3CD read with Rule 6G (1) (b) of Incometax Rules, 1962. Further, in terms of circular No 387 dated 6th July, 1984, the scope and effect audit under \r\nsection 44AB does not extend to investigational aspects of a case. We have conducted our verification of the statement in accordance with Guidance Note on Tax Audit under section 44AB of the Income-tax Act, 1961, issued by the ICAI which includes test checks and concept of materiality, and also requires that we comply with the ethical requirements of the code of ethics issued by the ICAI.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"In the absence of necessary details, we are unable to verify whether the cheques issued by the assessee were crossed account payee or not.","ObservationsCode":"09"},{"ObservationsVal":"Considering the significant complexities involved in the provisions relating to tax deduction at source under Chapter XVII-B of the Income tax Act, 1961, the computation of expenses admissible or inadmissible as per the provisions of Section 40(a), has been reviewed broadly and accordingly it has been broadly examined whether prima facie, the expenses claimed are admissible or inadmissible under this clause. As per the information supplied by the assessee, there are no amounts inadmissible under section 40(a). In this regard, we have relied upon the computation, information and explanations furnished to us by the assessee after performing review of systems and procedures relating to TDS, verification of large amounts / test verification of other amounts. (Clause 21(b)(ii) and 34 of Form 3CD)","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"As informed by the assessee, the information required under clause 44 of Form 3CD has not maintained in absence of any disclosure requirement thereof under the GST statute. Further the standard accounting software used by assessee is not configured to generate reports as required under the clause in absence of any prevailing statutory requirements and hence the figures reported under clause 44 are complied based on information as available in the books of accounts. We have verified these figures using our audit procedures which included test checks and concept of materiality.","ObservationsCode":"17"},{"ObservationsVal":"For the purpose of quantifying the disallowance In accordance with the provisions of Section 43B(h) of the Income Tax Act, 1961, as introduced by the Finance Act 2023, we have relied on the information and evidences provided by the management of the assessee in respect of registration of a supplier under the micro or small enterprise under the provisions of the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act, 2006.\n\nWe conducted our audit procedures using test checks and the concept of materiality to verify the representations made by management regarding payments to Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs) as defined under the MSMED Act, 2006 as to their coverage, classification and other terms. \n\n (Clause 22)","ObservationsCode":"11"},{"ObservationsVal":"Wherever there is no express agreement regarding the ?due date for payment? with the supplier or where such ?due date? was not appropriately captured in the accounting records of the assessee, then, as represented by the management and in line with the market scenario, the maximum permissible time limit of 45 days as stipulated in the MSMED Act was considered for the purpose of computing overdue payments. \n\nAdditionally, as represented by the management, wherever information about the registration or otherwise was not provided by the supplier despite multiple follow ups, those suppliers were considered as ?unregistered?, and no disallowance has been made in respect of those suppliers. \n\nAny instances of delayed payments identified during our procedures have been quantified for disallowance in the computation of taxable income for the relevant financial year and will be allowed as a deduction in the year of actual payment. (Clause 22)","ObservationsCode":"11"}]}},"Form3cdFlags":{"PrftLoassAcnt":"N","Sec145A":"N","VATPY":"N","SubClauseeofClause22":"N","ChangeInPartner":"N","BookOfAcnt":"N","SectionDed":"N","Section69D":"N","SalesTax":"N","IncurredExpenditure":"N","SubSec2Sec286":"N","ChangeNaturBuisnes":"N","Sec40A3A":"N","Sec201_1A_206_C7":"N","ChngShareSec79":"X","TaxPrescTime":"Y","IncomeCluaseixofsubsection2":"N","IncomeCluasexofsubsection2":"N","ChngMethodOfAcc":"N","TransferPriceSection92CE":"N","FurnishStatement":"N","ImpermissibleSec96":"N","Sec40A3":"Y","Form3cdSec562viiaFlag":"X","Form3cdSec562viibFlag":"N","ChapXVIIFlag":"Y","Sec145":"N"},"Form3cdUnpaidStrySec43b2Info":{"CsvDtls":{"HasMoreThan500":"false","Attachment":{"mimetype":"text/csv","hash":"12345"}}},"Form3cdTaxDedCollect":[{"TAN":"CMBV08061E","DueDateOfFurnish":"2023-09-30","TransactionsFlag":"Y","Typ